results.name: Decimal expansion of (5sqrt(3)+sqrt(15))/(6Pi).
comment: The ratio of the volume of a regular dodecahedron to the volume of the circumscribed sphere (which has circumradius a*(sqrt(3) + sqrt(15))/4 = a*(A002194 + A010472)/4, where a is the dodecahedron's edge length; see MathWorld link). For similar ratios for other Platonic solids, see A165922, A049541, A165952, and A165954. A063723 shows the order of these by size.
results.author: _Rick L. Shepherd_, Oct 02 2009
